reviews.review_text:
My Review .

I like this show.  It's a little loose in the beginning, but still great.  I think the show really gets cooking in the second half of the first set.  Bobby belts on Uncle and Big River and I dig the way Jerry gets into Stagger Lee.

I guess there are a few places where they lose the groove and seem a little off-tempo with each other, but I think it's a fine show.  Bobby is strong tonight.  There's some freakishness at the end of Victim that had me thinking I was in a flashback for a moment.  Pretty cool.  Then, right into a real sweet Bird Song.

It's hard for me to find negatives about any show outside of sound quality.  I love the band too much!  It's the little mistakes and the momentary losses of the groove that make them the humans they are.  What a great band, any show!  I am a bad critic, I suppose.

The sound quality of this show is great. I could hear everybody pretty good.  

.
